Algorithm grahamScanConvexHull(P, n)
Input: Array P of n points, each with x and y coordinates
Output: Convex hull points in counter-clockwise order

startIndex ← 0
for i ← 1 to n - 1 do
    if P[i].y < P[startIndex].y or
       (P[i].y = P[startIndex].y and P[i].x < P[startIndex].x) then
        startIndex ← i

Swap P[0] and P[startIndex]
startPoint ← P[0]

Sort P[1 to n-1] by polar angle with startPoint

stack ← empty stack
Push P[0] to stack
Push P[1] to stack
Push P[2] to stack

for i ← 3 to n - 1 do
    while size of stack ≥ 2 and cross(secondTop(stack), top(stack), P[i]) ≠ 2 do
        Pop from stack
    Push P[i] to stack

return stack
